OL,3,CDriver found guilty for killing dog
OL,4,Cwalker after losing control of vehicle
OL,6,FUpon leaving the industrial estate,
OL,7,FBoucher repeatedly revved his engine
OL,8,Ffor no apparent reason, with Mr
OL,9,FWilliams suggesting the defendant was
OL,10,F"showing off."
OL,12,FAs he reached a junction onto Ty Du
OL,13,FRoad, Boucher took a left at speed and
OL,14,Faccelerated as he made the turn.
OL,16,FProsecutor Owen Williams said the
OL,17,Fdefendant was travelling "way too
OL,18,Ffast" to negotiate the bend.
