OL,3,CDriver found guilty for killing dog
OL,4,Cwalker after losing control of vehicle
OL,6,FAt this point, Mr Chaplin was walking
OL,7,Ftwo dogs in the opposite direction of
OL,8,FBoucher's car as the defendant took
OL,9,Fthe left bend and "oversteered".
OL,11,FThis caused his rear tires to lose
OL,12,Fgrip, and the vehicle slid sideways
OL,13,Facross the road towards the pavement.
OL,15,FThe Peugeot mounted the pavement while
OL,16,Fsideways at an angle and collided with
OL,17,Fa lamppost, causing the vehicle to
OL,18,Fflip onto its side and come to a stop
OL,19,Fon a grass verge on the driver's side.
