OL,6,FScott Williams ran to help Boucher and
OL,7,Fopened the passenger door to help him
OL,8,Fclimb out of the vehicle. He was in a
OL,9,Fstate of shock and had an injury to
OL,10,Fhis head.
OL,12,FMr Chaplin was lying on his back on
OL,13,Fthe grass verge unconscious. He was
OL,14,Fbreathing but had been seriously
OL,15,Finjured.
OL,17,FScott Williams called an ambulance and
OL,18,Fbriefly returned to his workplace to
OL,19,Fget help as Boucher remained at the
OL,20,Fscene of the collision with Mr Chaplin.
